1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,000
abuelo, háblanos sobre las personas
caribeñas
----
grandpa, tell us about people
Caribbean

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Esta es nuestra zona de pesca, aquí mismo
Hemos traído a nuestros hijos
----
This is our fishing area, right here
We have brought our children

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Por eso nos hemos acostumbrado a esto
----
That's why we've gotten used to this

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Y no en lo que trabajan los arijunas (los que no son wayuu).
----
And not what the arijunas (those who are not wayuu) work on.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Este ha sido el oficio de nuestros padres y de
Nuestros abuelos
----
This has been the profession of our fathers and of
Our grandparents

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Aquí es donde siempre han pescado
----
This is where they have always fished

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Aquí
----
Here

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Cuando hay mucho viento la brisa empuja los insectos
Del monte hacia el mar
----
When there is a lot of wind the breeze pushes the insects
From the mountain to the sea

9
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Entonces, es más fácil pescar las sardinas como dicen
los arijunas y eso es lo que comemos en tiempos de verano.
----
So, it's easier to catch the sardines as they say
the arijunas and that is what we eat in summer times.

10
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Nuestro padre Juya (lluvio)no ha llegado por acá,
Nuestro abuelo
----
Our father Juya (rain) has not arrived here,
Our grandfather

11
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Por eso, hemos vivido de la pesca
y no en lo que trabajan los arijunas
----
For this reason, we have lived from fishing
and not what the arijunas work on

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Este ha sido nuestro oficio.
No sabemos lo que es robar
----
This has been our job.
We don't know what it is to steal

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Porque nuestros padres no nos inculcaron eso
----
Because our parents didn't teach us that.

14
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Solo nos alimentaron de lo que pescaban y es
Lo que hemos aprendido desde entonces
----
They only fed us what they caught and it is
What we have learned since then

15
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Una pregunta, ¿Cuál es la riqueza de un caribeño?
----
One question, what is the wealth of a Caribbean?

16
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Su riqueza es su oficio
----
Their wealth is their craft

17
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Lo que gana de su trabajo
----
What you earn from their job

18
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Porque con eso compran la lancha, la atarraya
----
Because with that they buy the boat, the cast net

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Si quiere tener animales, compra chivos y
Los tiene en otro territorio
----
If he wants to have animals, buy goats and
He has them in another territory

20
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Lejos del mar. Así, sus animales están allá y él acá.
----
Far from the sea Thus, his animals are there and he is here.

21
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Así es como deben ser las cosas
----
This is how things should be

22
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:02,000
En ese palo de allá y el de allá
----
On that stick over there and the one over there

23
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,000
los animales van directos
Allá y allá
----
animals go straight
there and there

24
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:15,000
No se pasan de ese punto, sino que se alimentan por acá
----
They do not go beyond that point, but they feed here

25
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Pueden pasar meses, años, los animales siempre
llegan a ese punto en el día
----
Months or years can go by, the animals always
get to that point in the day

26
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Incluso de noche, cuando salen las
estrellas esa es la señal de ellos
----
Even at night, when the
stars come out, that's their sign

27
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Siempre saben la zona donde van a comer
----
They always know the area where they are going to eat

28
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Se guían con el sonido del mar para ubicarse en la zona
----
They are guided by the sound of the sea to locate themselves in the area

29
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Así hacen en la noche
----
This is how they do at night

30
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Otra cosa que quería preguntar es si
----
Another thing I wanted to ask is if

31
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:01,000
¿En tiempos de verano suelen haber muchos peces o no?
----
In summer times there are usually many fish or not?

32
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:09,000
No, solo en aquellos momentos del día en
que no hay tanto viento
----
No, only at those times of the day when
that there is not so much wind

33
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Hay días en el que las mareas están quietas y así.
----
There are days when the tides are still and so on.

34
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Y en cuanto a los meses
----
And as for the months

35
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,000
¿Hay meses en los que hay abundancia de peces?
----
Are there months in which there is an abundance of fish?

36
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Si, duran meses porque tienen su hábitat acá
----
Yes, they last for months because they have their habitat here

37
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:36,000
En abril por lo general no hay peces
----
In April there are usually no fish

38
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Si porque los que se dedican a esto saben los meses
----
Yes, because those who are dedicated to this know the months

39
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:53,000
En el que hay peces y en los que no hay
----
In which there are fish and in which there are none

40
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
En los que no hay peces
----
where there are no fish

41
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Si claro, en abril como dice él,
----
Yes of course, in April as he says,

42
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:06,000
El viento es muy bueno para pescar
----
The wind is very good for fishing

43
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:15,000
El viento viene del suroeste y empuja las lanchas hacia allá
----
The wind comes from the southwest and pushes the boats there

44
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Poco a poco a mar adentro
----
Little by little into the sea

45
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Si eso es, muchas gracias, otra pregunta
----
Yes, that’s good, thank you very much, another question

46
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:50,000
Usted sabe que en nuestra cultura todo tiene
una connotación espiritual
----
You know that in our culture everything has
a spiritual connotation

47
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:58,000
los que vivimos en el monte cuando cazamos al
al conejo hay que tener en cuenta que hay unos espíritus
----
those of us who live in the mountains when we hunt the
rabbit it is necessary to take into account that there are some spirits

48
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Si lo cazamos frecuentemente se enojan esos espíritus
----
If we hunt him frequently, those spirits get angry

49
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,000
¿sucede lo mismo con el mar?
----
Does the same thing happen with the sea?

50
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Bueno, dicen que cuando una persona
pesca frecuentemente del mar le aparecen muchos peces
----
Well, they say that when a person fishes
Frequently from the sea many fish appear

51
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Mientras que para otros los peces se van al fondo
----
While for others the fish go to the bottom

52
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Es un espíritu que lo está atrayendo,
por eso se lo da solo a él
----
It is a spirit that is attracting him,
that's why he gives it only to him

53
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Y luego lo enferma
----
And then it makes him sick

54
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Le llega en cuerpo de mujer
----
It comes in a woman's body

55
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Le dice “vamos, vamos para allá” y cuando ya lo convence
----
He tells him "come on, let's go there" and when he is convinced

56
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Le da de comer algo para hechizarlo
----
He feeds him something to put a spell on him

57
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Y con eso hace que se acostumbre a ella.
----
And with that he gets used to her.

58
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Yo he escuchado el relato de un tío
----
I have heard the story of a guy

59
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:03,000
Que cuando ven que las olas se mueven demasiado
masticaban jawapi (planta medicinal)
----
That when they see that the waves move too much
they chewed jawapi (medicinal plant)

60
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
¿Por qué hacían eso?
----
Why did they do that?

61
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:12,000
No, es alouka (malambo)es para que lo deje tranquilo
----
No, it's alouka (malambo) it's for it to leave him alone

62
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,000
para que el espíritu esté contento
----
so that the spirit is happy

63
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Se alegra si le traen algo, se lo tiran al mar
----
It is happy if they bring it something, they throw it into the sea

64
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:27,000
Y le tiene que pedir que les regale peces y ya.
----
And you have to ask it to give you fish and that's it.

65
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Es cierto, esa es la connotación espiritual que tiene
Por eso no se debe correr a pescar por pescar
----
It's true, that's the spiritual connotation it has.
That's why you shouldn't rush to fish just for the sake of fishing

66
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Porque si no se pierde.
----
Because if you do, you lose.

67
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Y así es con lo demás, si en una mudanza no
se sacrifica el chivo por la llegada
----
And so it goes, if when moving a goat
is not sacrificed for the arrival

68
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,000
Puede sufrir un daño por un clavo o zinc.
----
It can be damaged by a nail or zinc.

69
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,000
Si, todo tiene un ritual
----
Yes, everything has a ritual

70
00:06:54,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Tiene una connotación espiritual, sí.
----
It has a spiritual connotation, yes.

71
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,000
¿Para mantener la armonía no?
----
To maintain harmony, right?

72
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Si claro, para alegrar el territorio
----
Yes of course, to brighten up the territory

73
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Alegrar la tierra.
----
Brighten the Earth.

74
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Si se muda debe hacer el ritual de la comelona
para armonizar la convivencia también
----
If you’re moving, you must do “la comelona” (a big feast)
to harmonize coexistence as well

75
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Otra cosa, digo, otra pregunta
----
Another thing, I mean, another question

76
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:56,000
¿antes había más peces o es igual que ahora?
----
Was there more fish before or is it the same as now?

77
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,000
No, son poquitos
----
no, there are fewer now

78
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:03,000
Háblanos de eso para que quede grabado en la cámara
----
Tell us about it so it's recorded on camera

79
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:09,000
Ya no hay peces como antes, por eso se pesca poco ahora
----
There are no longer as many fish as before, that's why there is little fishing now

80
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Si pescamos, regresamos con poquito
----
If we fish, we return with little

81
00:08:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Como es poquito no se gana casi nada con eso,
apenas si alcanza para la comida
----
As it is little, you gain almost nothing with it,
barely enough for food

82
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:29,000
Además, hay mucha gente pescando hoy en día.
----
Also, there are a lot of people fishing nowadays.

83
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:38,000
También las nuevas lanchas con motores
Johnson hacen mucho ruido
----
Also, the new boats with
Johnson motors make a lot of noise

84
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Ese ruido hace dispersar los peces,
----
That noise makes the fish scatter,

85
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,000
sí es cierto.
----
Yes it's correct.
